ABEOKUTA- All hell was let loose, Tuesday, at Kikelomo area in Ayetoro, Yewa North Local Government when a stray bullet killed one person while three others sustained injuries during a fracas between men of the Nigeria Customs Service and suspected smugglers in the area. Independent gathered that men of the customs service were in the area following a tip off of smuggling activities by some suspected smugglers. It was gathered that some of the youths had mounted roadblocks to prevent the Customs officers from accessing the area. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! An eyewitness account had it that the fracas escalated when the officers came to the scene and had to fire shots to clear their way from the roadblocks. The deceased who was later identified as Sola Soga, it was gathered, was pacifying other youths not to prevent the Customs officers from their official duty before he was later hit and killed by the bullet. NEMA Urges Motorists To Observe Speed Limit, Road Signs Yuletide: FRSC Deploys 1,250 Personnel In Enugu The eye-witness reported, “Customs officers were going to their duty post when some youths formed a road block to stop them. The guy that was shot was one of the guys that came to appeal to the youths to allow the officers go about their duty. “He was hit by a stray bullet when the officers started shooting.” Another eye witness account had it that the officers successfully accessed an illegal warehouse in the area before the owner of the warehouse arrived and was trying to strike a deal with the officers. This, the eyewitness said, attracted many alleged smugglers into scene in solidarity with their colleagues which led to shooting by the officers to clear their ways for successful movement of the confiscated goods. He said, it was in the process Soga was hot by the bullet and died on the spot while others sustained injuries. Independent further m gathered that the violence took another dimension when some youths from the village of the deceased arrived the scene with dangerous weapons and attacked the security officers. When contacted, the NCS Public Relations Officer for the Federal Operations Unit, Ikeja Lagos, Peter Duniya, confirmed the development. Duniya, who said he was yet to be properly briefed of the details, promised to get back in a later time. When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi confirmed the development. Oyeyemi further confirmed the death on Soga adding that the Commissioner of Police, Edward Ajogun, had directed the Area Commander in the area to move into the scene and douse the tension. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION